<P><H1 align=center>ADD/EDIT DECLINED MORTGAGE DETAILS – DC121</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>fields shown in red are mandatory and must be completed to 
proceed</FONT>           </P>
<P><H3>Declined Mortgage Owner: </H3>Select the name of the applicant who has had a 
previous mortgage application declined, from the drop down list. If it is a sole 
application, the name of the applicant will be pre-completed.</P>
<P><H3>Date Declined: </H3>Input the date the mortgage 
application was declined by the lender.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Details: </H3>Input all the details of the application, 
including the name of the lender and the reason they declined the application. 
These details are required as they may affect the suitability of the applicant 
for a mortgage, and/or their credit rating.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Are there any Additional Applicants: </H3>Click the 
‘Yes’ radio button if the application declined was in more than the one name, 
and include their details in the box below.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Another: </H3>If there was more than one declined 
application, click the ‘Another’ button, which will take you to a new details 
screen. Input all details as above.
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>When all declined mortgage details have been 
completed, click the ‘OK’ button to return to the previous screen.
<P></P>
